00:00:03.380 --> 00:00:06.040
We're going to talk about how
your gastrointestinal tract

00:00:06.040 --> 00:00:09.800
behaves in an altered pressure
environment-- airplane farts.

00:00:15.824 --> 00:00:18.230
Her, frequent flyers,
Trace here for "D News."

00:00:18.230 --> 00:00:20.160
Before I leave for
CES today, I posed

00:00:20.160 --> 00:00:22.230
a question to my
"D News" fellows--

00:00:22.230 --> 00:00:24.710
do we fart more on planes?

